===Etymology===
Via {{ME.}} from {{OE.}} ''[[dæġ]]'' < {{PG.}} '''[[*dagaz]]''' < Proto-Indo-European '''[[*dhegh-]]''' (to burn). Not related to Latin '''dies''' (which is from PIE base '''[[*dyeu-]]''' [to shine]), but rather to Sanskrit '''dāhas''' (heat), which came from PIE '''[[*dhegh-]]''' (to burn). Cognates include Swedish [[dag]] and German [[Tag]] (day).

