===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A period of 24 [[hour]]s.
# The period from [[midnight]] to the following [[midnight]]. There are 7 days in a week: [[Sunday]], [[Monday]], [[Tuesday]], [[Wednesday]], [[Thursday]], [[Friday]], and [[Saturday]].
# Rotational period of a planet (especially [[earth]]).
# The part of a day(3) which one spends at one’s job, school, etc. The meaning of "I worked two days last week" is not the same as "I worked 48 hours last week." With hours, only the hours spent working are counted. With days, if a full shift is worked, it is counted as a day.
# Period of day<sup>3</sup> between sunrise and sunset where one enjoys daylight. Daytime. Re: "day and night".

